# Parallel work: serial test execution

At most **one** pytest or Makefile test process repo-wide at any time. Concurrent `make test-fast` from multiple Multitask workers can lock WSL2 workstations.

## Roles

| Role | Tests |
|------|-------|
| **Executor (worker)** | **Targeted only** — smallest pytest/Makefile command covering touched paths |
| **Coordinator (parent)** | **`make test-fast`** after each `land-issue` on repo root `main` |

## Executor (hard prohibitions)

- Do **not** run `make test-fast`, `make test`, `make test-jax`, or bare `uv run --group dev pytest` (full suite).
- Check the **terminals folder** before pytest; if another test is running, defer and report `tests deferred to coordinator`.
- Run multiple targeted commands **serially** in one worker, never parallel pytest.
- Hand off: targeted command + pass/fail (or deferred); do **not** claim full-suite coverage.

## Coordinator

1. Workers commit in worktrees; coordinator runs `land-issue`.
2. Confirm no executor pytest is running.
3. Run **`make test-fast`** once per landed issue (serial).
4. Do not start the next batch or next land until `make test-fast` finishes.
5. Optional `uv run ow train …` smoke — serial only, after pytest, when train/CLI/submission touched.

